article.headline: Dartmouth 64, Alaska-Anchorage 52
article.story: ANCHORAGE, Alaska -- David Rufful had 19 points, including three 3-pointers, and seven rebounds to lead Dartmouth to a 64-52 victory Friday over Alaska-Anchorage in a Great Alaska Shootout consolation game. Jvonte Brooks added 13 points and 10 rebounds, and Jabari Trotter scored 12 as the Big Green (2-3) broke open a close game after halftime. Travis Thompson had 11 points and Phillip Hearn scored 10 for the Seawolves (0-2). The game was tied 25-25 at halftime, and Alaska-Anchorage was within two points, 32-30, after Taylor Rohde made one of two free throws with 15:57 to play. But Dartmouth responded with a 20-5 run over the next 10 minutes to put the game away. Dartmouth's opponent Saturday will be the winner of the Central Michigan-UC Irvine game later Friday, and Alaska-Anchorage will play the loser of that game.
